To show how greatly scansion depended on accent eius, huius, quoius, are indifferently used as trochees, pyrrhics, or mono- syllables. Compounds in which two vowels come together are regularly contracted, e.g. ere-O'ptare. Double letters were prob- ably not written in the time of Plautus, and consequently vowels when unaccented are freely shortened before double consonants: deculto 712, decepisti 964, satalites 833, Philippicas 152.
